%U A395764 5566905178101890203492759680,135668733539484402850180633516800,4442822430221767620483566426087942400,190386370568065993499378810291075536665600
%N A395764 First column of the triangular array with T(0, m) = m! and T(n, m) = T(n - 1, m + 3) - 2*T(n - 1, m + 2) + T(n - 1, m + 1).
%C A395764 a(n) is the first entry in the n-th row of a triangular array built from the factorial sequence, where T(0, m) = m! and each subsequent row T(n, m) is obtained by T(n - 1, m + 3) - 2*T(n - 1, m + 2) + T(n - 1, m + 1).
%C A395764 The rows are generated by iterating the operator E*Delta^2, where E is the forward shift operator, E(f(m)) = f(m + 1), and Delta = E - 1 is the forward difference operator. Equivalently, E*Delta^2 = E*(E - 1)^2 = E^3 - 2*E^2 + E.
%C A395764 This is the (p, q) = (2, 1) case of the family obtained by iterating E^q*Delta^p on the factorial sequence.
%F A395764 Let f(m) = m!. Then
%F A395764 a(n) = ((E*Delta^2)^n f)(0).
%F A395764 a(n) = Sum_{j=0..2*n} (-1)^j*binomial(2*n, j)*(3*n - j)!.
%F A395764 a(n) = Integral_{t=0..oo} t^n*(t - 1)^(2*n)*exp(-t) dt.
%F A395764 More generally, if b_{p,q}(n) = ((E^q*Delta^p)^n f)(0), where f(m) = m!, then b_{p,q}(n) = Integral_{t=0..oo} t^(q*n)*(t - 1)^(p*n)*exp(-t) dt = Sum_{j=0..p*n} (-1)^j*binomial(p*n, j)*((p + q)*n - j)!.
%F A395764 a(n) ~ sqrt(2*Pi) * 3^(3*n + 1/2) * n^(3*n + 1/2) / exp(3*n + 2/3). - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, May 13 2026
%e A395764 First column of
%e A395764   n=0:         1          1           2            6          24       120     720  5040
%e A395764   n=1:         3         14          78          504        3720     30960  287280
%e A395764   n=2:       362       2790       24024       229080     2399760  27422640
%e A395764   n=3:    183822    1965624    22852200    287250480  3884393520
%e A395764   n=4: 243511704 3332744760 48773612880 760381337520
%t A395764 Table[Sum[(-1)^j * Binomial[2*n, j] * (3*n - j)!, {j,0,2*n}], {n,0,20}] (* _Vaclav Kotesovec_, May 13 2026 *)
